output/*.mp4
output/*.png
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.env

# NOTE: output/used_*.json is deliberately COMMITTED (it used to be ignored).
# It's the memory of which questions have already aired. The cloud runner is wiped
# after every run, so if this isn't in the repo the bot forgets everything it has
# posted and starts repeating itself immediately — on a channel posting daily,
# forever.

# NOTE: assets/images/ and assets/art/ are deliberately COMMITTED. Every picture
# in there has been reviewed by eye, and both sources are non-deterministic — the
# stock library's results drift and the art model returns something new each time —
# so re-fetching in the cloud would ship pictures nobody ever looked at. (An early
# unreviewed fetch turned up a wine bottle and a 3D pin-up.) Committing them also
# keeps the cloud from spending ~45s per image on every run.

# YouTube OAuth secrets — NEVER commit these
client_secret.json
yt_token.json
yt_token.json.bak
